This paper deals with online learning and multitask learning, which are topics that are commonly studied in the machine learning community. The paper also discusses distributed and collaborative learning, which is a subfield of machine learning that focuses on learning in networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses regularization, which is a technique commonly used in optimization problems, so cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a possible category. Finally, the paper presents simulations to illustrate the theoretical findings, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
